## JADX
What it is: JADX is a decompiler that converts Android DEX (Dalvik Executable) files into readable Java source code.
Key Features:

  -Converts APK, DEX, and AAR files to Java source code
  -Provides both GUI and command-line interfaces
  -Handles obfuscated code (to some extent)
  -Shows bytecode alongside decompiled Java

## Primary use
# GUI mode - best for exploring
jadx-gui app.apk

# Command line - good for automation
jadx -d output/ app.apk


## What can you find there
  -Hardcoded API keys and passwords
  -Insecure code patterns (WebView with JavaScript enabled)
  -Custom SSL/TLS implementations
  -Third-party libraries used
  -Business logic and authentication flows

## Limitations 
    -Obfuscated code may not decompile perfectly
    -Some code may show as "// TODO: decompile failed"
    -Cannot recover original variable names if obfuscated
